==English==

===Etymology===
[[re-]] "again, back" + [[wind]] "turn".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/riˈwaɪnd/}}, {{SAMPA|/ri"waInd/}}

*'''Hyphenation:''' re·wind
*'''Rhymes:''' [[Rhymes:English:-aɪnd|-aɪnd]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|rewinds|rewinding|rewound}}

# To [[wind]] [[back]]; as, to rewind a [[VCR]], [[cassette]] [[tape]], or [[DVD]].
# To wind [[again]]; as, to rewind an unwound [[spool]] of [[string]] or [[tape]].

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[terugspoelen]] (1)

[[Category:English ergative verbs]]
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of rewinding.
# A [[button]] or other [[mechanism]] for rewinding.
#:''I meant to pause the picture, but hit the '''rewind''' by mistake.''

